  "texts": [
    "Solving a maths problem and remembering to do something (i.e., laying down a 'memory trace') are cognitive activities performed by cognitive agents.",
    "So, on the face of it, they are activities that meet the broad criteria outlined in (§2.1) -they are bits of information processing directed to cognitive ends according to a means-end structure characteristic of cognitive agency.",
    "So, the thought is that the environmental and bodily resources that mediate these effects, and so realise these ends, are intimately involved the kinds of human cognitive agency that depend on offloading.",
    "Schematically, the argument is as follows:",
    "P1 If cognitive offloading is pervasive in and transformative of human cognition, it constitutes some human cognition."
  ],
